definitions.definition: To flow over the brim of (a container ).
examples: The river overflowed the levee into the road.

definitions.definition: To cover with a liquid , literally or figuratively .
examples: The flash flood overflowed most of the parkland and some homes.

definitions.definition: To cause an overflow . (Can we add an example for this sense?)
To flow over the edge of a container .
examples: The waters overflowed into the Ninth Ward.
The hospital ER was overflowing with flu cases.

subdefinitions.definition: To (cause to) exceed the available numeric range .
examples: Calculating 255+1 will overflow an eight-bit byte.

definitions.definition: To be superabundant ; to abound ; to ooze.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To flow over the brim of (a container ).
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To cover with a liquid , literally or figuratively .
( transitive ) To cause an overflow . (Can we add an example for this sense?)
( intransitive ) To flow over the edge of a container .
( intransitive ) To exceed limits or capacity .
( intransitive ) To be superabundant ; to abound ; to ooze.
